The paper deals with compressed representation and learning in Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a new method for compressing CNNs, which involves using fixed filters and one-dimensional filters, which could be considered a form of neural architecture search (cs.AI) or optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper applies the method to four well-known network architectures, which could be considered a form of experimental evaluation (cs.MM).
